    },
    {
      "text": "Mary-Kate and Ashley: Pocket Planner is a digital planner and video game developed by American studio Powerhead Games and published by Acclaim Entertainment. It was released on November 21, 2000, for the Game Boy Color. It is part of the Mary-Kate and Ashley video game series. The user can keep track of the time and take notes while also playing through a number of minigames. Mary-Kate and Ashley are featured extensively throughout the planner. Reception was mixed, with criticism focused on the shortcomings of the game and its gendered focus and content while praising its clever features.",
